The paper deals with the problem of estimating the size of independent sets in a graph defined by a stream of edges. This problem is related to graph algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), as well as to graph theory (cs.GT) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) to derive lower bounds on the performance of algorithms. Finally, the paper presents results on the accuracy of the approximation, which could be of interest to researchers working on computational complexity (cs.CC).
